        <p>Payments are processed through secure third-party payment processors. By providing payment information, you authorize us to charge the applicable fees.</p>

        <h3>4.3 Late Payments</h3>
        <p>Late payments may result in service interruption. A late fee may be applied to overdue accounts.</p>

        <h3>4.4 Refunds</h3>
        <p>Refunds are provided at our discretion. Cancellations made more than 48 hours before a scheduled inspection are eligible for a full refund. Cancellations within 48 hours may incur a cancellation fee.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Scheduling and Cancellation</h2>
        <h3>5.1 Scheduling</h3>
        <p>Inspections must be scheduled at least 48 hours in advance. We will make reasonable efforts to accommodate your preferred date and time.</p>

        <h3>5.2 Cancellation Policy</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>48+ hours notice:</strong> Full refund or reschedule at no charge</li>
          <li><strong>24-48 hours notice:</strong> 50% cancellation fee or reschedule with $25 fee</li>
          <li><strong>Less than 24 hours notice:</strong> No refund, full cancellation fee applies</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.3 Property Access</h3>
        <p>You are responsible for ensuring property access during scheduled inspections. If access cannot be obtained, it will be treated as a cancellation with less than 24 hours notice.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Inspection Reports and Documentation</h2>
        <h3>6.1 Report Delivery</h3>
        <p>Inspection reports are typically delivered within 24 hours of the inspection. Reports include photo documentation and detailed findings.</p>

        <h3>6.2 Report Accuracy</h3>
        <p>While we strive for accuracy, our inspections are visual assessments and may not identify all issues. We do not guarantee that all defects will be discovered.</p>

        <h3>6.3 Report Ownership</h3>
        <p>You retain ownership of your inspection reports and photos. We retain a copy for our records and quality assurance purposes.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Limitations of Liability</h2>
        <h3>7.1 Service Limitations</h3>
        <p>Our inspections are limited to visual assessments of accessible areas. We do not:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Perform invasive or destructive testing</li>
          <li>Inspect areas that are inaccessible or unsafe</li>
          <li>Predict future conditions or lifespan of components</li>
          <li>Provide cost estimates for repairs</li>
          <li>Determine code compliance</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Liability Cap</h3>
        <p>Our total liability for any claims arising from our services shall not exceed the amount paid for the specific inspection in question, up to a maximum of $1,000.</p>

        <h3>7.3 No Warranties</h3>
        <p>Services are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. We do not warrant that inspections will be error-free or that all defects will be identified.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
